com.github.jpmsilva.groundlevel.utilities

Class QuackAnnotationAwareOrderComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.core.OrderComparator
      • com.github.jpmsilva.groundlevel.utilities.QuackAnnotationAwareOrderComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparator<Object>

    public class QuackAnnotationAwareOrderComparator
extends org.springframework.core.OrderComparator
    If it looks like Ordered, then it must be Ordered. This specialized OrderComparator performs comparisons similar to AnnotationAwareOrderComparator, but with some key differences.

    1) the Order annotation is always checked first.

    2) if the Order annotation is added to the bean producer method, it will also be checked, and take precedence over the annotation at the bean class level. If multiple bean producer methods contribute the same instance to the bean factory, the behavior is unspecified.

    3) beans do not need to implement Ordered, they simply need to have a public method with the signature int getOrder(), and that method will be used to also determine the order value.
